## Reading Documentation Before Writing Any Code

Always read the authentication section of any API's docs first — no request succeeds without correct credentials, and most early debugging time is wasted on auth errors that a careful first read would have prevented. The error code reference is the second most valuable section: knowing that 401 means bad authentication, 403 means authenticated but forbidden, and 422 means the request structure is right but validation failed turns confusing failures into quick fixes rather than guesswork.
